	 New Delhi, Sept. 16: Former Union law minister Shanti Bhushan today told the Supreme Court that of 16 past Chief Justices of India, eight were definitely corrupt.          
	Bhushan said in an affidavit filed in the apex court that six of the chief justices were definitely honest and nothing could be said either way about the remaining two.          
	The former minister gave the names of the judges in a sealed cover to a bench hearing a contempt petition against his son Prashant Bhushan.           
	He said he was going public with this statement so that he, too, would have to face contempt-of-court proceedings.           ti Bhushan claimed two former chief justices had told him their immediate predecessors and successors were corrupt. He said he had included the names of these four chief justices in his list of eight.                  
	 New Delhi: Yashwant Sinha on Thursday resigned as the BJPs Punjab minder because of his preoccupation with work as chairman of the parliamentary standing committee on finance, a source close to him said. Sinha, elected as an MP from Jharkhand, had made no secret of his resentment at being passed up for the job of chief minister in the states new BJP-led government.                  
	 New Delhi: Vinod Sinha, an aide of former Jharkhand chief minister Madhu Koda and a co-accused in the Rs 4,000-crore money-laundering scam, has been arrested by the CBI in Delhi.                                                                                                                                              
